info.headline: Flood Warning issued July 9 at 9:30AM CDT until July 13 at 7:00AM CDT by NWS Twin Cities/Chanhassen MN
info.description:
...The Flood Warning is extended for the following rivers in Minnesota...
Minnesota River near Jordan affecting Scott, Carver and Sibley Counties.
...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in Minnesota...
Minnesota River at New Ulm affecting Brown, Nicollet and Blue Earth Counties.
Minnesota River at Granite Falls HWY 212 affecting Chippewa, Yellow Medicine and Renville Counties.
Minnesota River at Morton affecting Redwood and Renville Counties.
Minnesota River at Montevideo affecting Chippewa, Yellow Medicine and Lac qui Parle Counties.
...The Flood Warning is cancelled for the following rivers in Minnesota...
Crow River at Rockford affecting Wright and Hennepin Counties.
* WHAT...Minor flooding is forecast.
* WHERE...Minnesota River near Jordan.
* WHEN...From Friday morning to Sunday morning.
* IMPACTS...At 25.0 feet, Low lying areas and some roads along the river begin to flood and private sanitary sewers may experience problems.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 745 AM CDT Wednesday, the stage was 24.8 feet. - Forecast...The river is expected to rise to a crest of 25.0 feet Friday morning. It will then fall below flood stage early Saturday afternoon. - Flood stage is 25.0 feet.
info.instruction:
Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles.
Caution is urged when walking near riverbanks.

parameter.value: FLOOD WARNING NOW IN EFFECT FROM FRIDAY MORNING TO SUNDAY MORNING
